last_episode_to_air.name: Mijacogeo (a.k.a. The Frodis Caper)
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Monkees match wits with the insane Wizard Glick (Rip Taylor), who is out to control the minds of television viewers worldwide.

name: The Monkees
overview: Micky, Mike, Peter, and Davy are four young men in mid-1960s LA, members of a struggling country-folk-rock band looking for their big break amid madcap encounters with a variety of people straight out of TV and movie central casting, with full knowledge that their existence is part of a weekly television series
tagline: Who's putting who on? You'll never know till you see this show!

episodes.name: The Royal Flush
episodes.overview: The Monkees rescue Princess Bettina, Duchess of Harmonica (Katherine Walsh) from her evil uncle Archduke Otto (Theodore Marcuse).

episodes.name: Monkee See, Monkee Die
episodes.overview: The Monkees spend the night in a haunted house to collect an inheritance.

episodes.name: Monkee vs. Machine
episodes.overview: In a computerized toy factory, the Monkees foil an efficiency expert (Stan Freberg) who wants to replace an old toymaker (Walter Janovitz) with automation.

episodes.name: Your Friendly Neighborhood Kidnappers
episodes.overview: A shady PR man (Andre Philippe) kidnaps the Monkees to prevent them from winning a talent contest in order for his clients (rival band the Four Swines) to win.

episodes.name: The Spy Who Came in From the Cool
episodes.overview: The Monkees get mixed up in a spy ring (Jacques Aubuchon, Arlene Martel) after Davy accidentally purchases a set of red maracas containing secret microfilm. Can the Monkees outwit two professional spies ?

episodes.name: Success Story
episodes.overview: Davy's grandfather (Ben Wright) visits, and the Monkees try to convince him that his grandson is wealthy and successful.

episodes.name: The Monkees in a Ghost Town
episodes.overview: Stranded in a ghost town after their car runs out of gas, the Monkees are held prisoner by bank robbers (Len Lesser, Lon Chaney Jr.) and their boss, "The Big Man" (Rose Marie).

episodes.name: Don't Look a Gift Horse in the Mouth (a.k.a. Gift Horse)
episodes.overview: Davy is given a horse, which the Monkees have to hide from their landlord, Mr. Babbitt (Henry Corden). It is returned to a heart-broken child (Kerry MacLane) and father (Jim Boles) after Davy rides it to victory over the horse of the father's neighbor. Famed character actor, and frequent Bob Hope sideman, Jerry Colonna plays veterinarian Doctor Mann.

episodes.name: The Chaperone
episodes.overview: Davy's feelings for retired General Harley Vandenberg's (Arch Johnson) daughter Leslie (Sherry Alberoni) leads Micky to pose as a female chaperone at a party after the real chaperone (Diana Chesney) gets drunk.

episodes.name: Here Come the Monkees
episodes.overview: The Monkees play a sweet sixteen party and help the birthday girl (Robyn Millan) with her studies after she falls for Davy.

episodes.name: Monkees à la Carte
episodes.overview: The Monkees pose as the Purple Flower Gang to save their favourite Italian restaurant from a gangster (Harvey Lembeck).

episodes.name: I've Got a Little Song Here
episodes.overview: Mike is fleeced by a fraudulent music publisher (Phil Leeds), but Micky dons the guise of a flashy Hollywood producer to get Mike's money back.

episodes.name: One Man Shy
episodes.overview: Bashful Peter tries to win the heart of lovely debutante Valerie Cartwright (Lisa James) while dealing with her haughty boyfriend Ronnie Farnsworth (George Furth).

episodes.name: Dance, Monkee, Dance
episodes.overview: The Monkees sign up for lessons at Renaldo's Dance Au Go Go (Hal March), and then find out that their contracts are for life.

episodes.name: Too Many Girls (a.k.a. Davy and Fern)
episodes.overview: A domineering stage mother (Reta Shaw) tries to use Davy to further her daughter Fern's (Kelly Jean Peters) career.

episodes.name: Son of a Gypsy
episodes.overview: A band of gypsies, headed by the powerful Maria (Jeanne Arnold), force the Monkees to steal a priceless statuette called the "Maltese Vulture."

episodes.name: The Case of the Missing Monkee
episodes.overview: Peter becomes involved with the disappearance of the respected Professor Milo Schnitzler (Norbert Schiller) and then disappears himself.

episodes.name: I Was a Teenage Monster
episodes.overview: A mad scientist (John Hoyt) hires the Monkees to teach his monster (Richard Kiel) music—and then transplants their musical talent into the monster. Can the Monkees get their talent back? Byron Foulger appears as Groot, Dr. Mendoza's assistant.

episodes.name: Find the Monkees
episodes.overview: When television producer Hubbell Bensen (Carl Ballantine) hears a tape of the Monkees, he frantically stages auditions in the hope of finding them for his new television show, unaware they are desperately trying to audition for him.

episodes.name: Monkees in the Ring
episodes.overview: A crooked fight promoter (Ned Glass) prepares to cash in on a big bet by making Davy a stooge in a bout with the champ.

episodes.name: The Prince and the Paupers
episodes.overview: Davy doubles for a lookalike Peruvian prince in order to win the heart of Wendy Forsythe (Heather North) or forfeit his throne to evil Count Myron (Oscar Beregi Jr.).

episodes.name: Monkees at the Circus
episodes.overview: To save a bankrupt circus, the Monkees pose as a troupe of dazzling, supreme high-wire artists from France known as the Mozzarelli Brothers, but get in trouble when their guise requires them to actually perform.

episodes.name: Captain Crocodile
episodes.overview: The Monkees' appearance on popular children's show The Captain Crocodile Show is sabotaged by its host (Joey Forman), who fears that his guest's popularity is diminishing his own.

episodes.name: Monkees à la Mode
episodes.overview: The Monkees are chosen as "Typical Young Americans of the Year," by Chic magazine, a haughty publication that runs a bogus article on the group moulding them into a false image of clean cut young men.

episodes.name: Alias Micky Dolenz
episodes.overview: The police cash in on Micky's striking resemblance to imprisoned crime kingpin Baby Face Morales in an attempt to locate robbery loot.

episodes.name: Monkees Chow Mein
episodes.overview: Peter finds a secret message in a fortune cookie at a Chinese restaurant, forcing Monkeemen Davy and Mike to come to his rescue from the evil Dragonman (Joey Forman).

episodes.name: Monkee Mother
episodes.overview: Middle-aged widow Millie (Rose Marie) moves in with the Monkees as a new tenant, resulting in the boys' trying to find her a husband.

episodes.name: The Monkees on the Line
episodes.overview: Hired by a telephone answering service, the Monkees are soon plunged into mix-ups, hang-ups and crossed wires leading to pursuit by a crooked bettor (Milton Frome).

episodes.name: The Monkees Get Out More Dirt
episodes.overview: The Monkees' friendship is threatened when they all fall for the same girl, luscious local laundromat proprietress April Conquest (Julie Newmar).

episodes.name: The Monkees in Manhattan (a.k.a. The Monkees Manhattan Style)
episodes.overview: In New York City, the Monkees fend off an irate hotel manager (Philip Ober) as they help a producer (Richard Anders) get backing for a Broadway musical.

episodes.name: The Monkees at the Movies
episodes.overview: The Monkees have a run-in with a snobbish movie idol (Bobby Sherman) on the set as extras in a beach movie.

episodes.name: The Monkees on Tour
episodes.overview: A mini-documentary chronicling a live Monkees concert gig on location in Phoenix, Arizona during their first public appearance tour.

episodes.name: A Nice Place to Visit
episodes.overview: In El Monotono, Mexico, Davy is captured by a bandito (Peter Whitney) and his minions for being "captivated" with El Diablo's girlfriend (Cynthia Hull).

episodes.name: The Picture Frame (a.k.a. The Bank Robbery)
episodes.overview: Peter must prove the Monkees' innocence when they unwittingly rob a bank in the pretext of making a movie for two con men (Cliff Norton, Kelton Garwood).

episodes.name: Everywhere a Sheik, Sheik
episodes.overview: It is a "harem-scare 'em" scene as Davy faces the prospect of marriage to a lovely Nehudian princess (Donna Loren).

episodes.name: Monkee Mayor
episodes.overview: Mike casts his wool hat into the ring to stop a crooked construction tycoon (Monte Landis) from turning the city into parking lots.

episodes.name: Art for Monkees' Sake
episodes.overview: At an art museum, Peter copies an old painting for two guards (Monte Landis, Vic Tayback) who are actually thieves bent on snatching the real painting.

episodes.name: I Was A 99 Pound Weakling
episodes.overview: After losing his girlfriend Brenda to a muscle man named Bulk, Micky starts a health program under the guidance of fraudulent physical cultist Shah-Ku (Monte Landis).

episodes.name: Hillbilly Honeymoon (a.k.a. Double Barrel Shotgun Wedding)
episodes.overview: Lost in Swineville, the Monkees get caught in the middle of a hillbilly feud between the Weskitts and Chubbers with Davy staring down the barrel of a shotgun wedding to pretty Ella Mae Chubber (Melody Patterson).

episodes.name: Monkees Marooned
episodes.overview: Peter trades his guitar for a con man’s treasure map. On a deserted island, the Monkees go hunting for treasure—and are hunted by a mad Australian (Monte Landis) and his man Thursday (Rupert Crosse).

episodes.name: The Card Carrying Red Shoes
episodes.overview: Peter is the target of a romantic prima ballerina (Ondine Vaughn) and a dastardly plot choreographed by the rest of the ballet company.

episodes.name: Wild Monkees
episodes.overview: The Monkees turn chicken when they unwittingly befriend the girlfriends of a tough motorcycle gang.

episodes.name: A Coffin Too Frequent
episodes.overview: A mad scientist (George Furth), his goony cousin (Mickey Morton), and his dotty aunt (Ruth Buzzi) use the Monkees' pad for a séance to summon their relative Elmer from beyond.

episodes.name: Hitting the High Seas
episodes.overview: Thoughts of mutiny are bountiful as the Monkees try to stop the hijack of a cargo ship by a vengeful sea captain (Chips Rafferty).

episodes.name: Monkees in Texas
episodes.overview: In the Lone Star State, the Monkees outwit Black Bart (Barton MacLane), his cohort Red (Len Lesser) and the gang to save Mike's Aunt Kate's (Jacqueline deWit) ranch.

episodes.name: Monkees on the Wheel
episodes.overview: In Las Vegas, the Monkees are mistaken for crooked gamblers by a roulette dealer (Rip Taylor) and policeman (Dort Clark) and try their luck at exposing the real gang (David Astor and Pepper Davis).

episodes.name: The Christmas Show
episodes.overview: The Monkees try to instil the spirit of Christmas in a cynical little boy (Butch Patrick) who has soured on the whole idea.

episodes.name: Fairy Tale
episodes.overview: A Monkee pantomime romp through Fairy Tale Land, introduced by a "Town Crier" (Rege Cordic), sees Peter rescuing a haughty princess (Michael) from death by her fiendish fiancee (Murray Roman).

episodes.name: Monkees Watch Their Feet
episodes.overview: A documented film report by the Department of UFO Information, headed by Pat Paulsen, shows the Monkees foiling an invasion by aliens (Stuart Margolin and Nita Talbot) from Planet Zlotnick.

episodes.name: Monstrous Monkee Mash
episodes.overview: The Monkees attempt to rescue Davy from his girlfriend Lorelei (Arlene Martel), Count Batula (Ron Masak), a wolf man (David Pearl), mummy man, and a Frankenstein-looking monster in a creepy castle.

episodes.name: Monkees Paw
episodes.overview: A broken-down magician's (Hans Conried) magical monkey's paw starts to bring the equally broken Monkees luck... unfortunately, all bad.

episodes.name: The Devil and Peter Tork
episodes.overview: At an eerie pawn shop, Peter unwittingly sells his soul to devilish character Mr. Zero (Monte Landis) in order to purchase a golden harp! Can Peter's musical talent save him from Mr. Zero's evil clutches forever ?

episodes.name: Monkees Race Again (a.k.a. Leave the Driving to Us)
episodes.overview: Davy drives the Monkeemobile in an auto race when the British entry is sabotaged by Baron Von Klutz (David Hurst) and his Klutzmobile. Featuring a cameo appearance by co-producer Bob Rafelson as the "World's Oldest Flower Child."

episodes.name: Monkees in Paris (a.k.a. The Paris Show)
episodes.overview: The Monkees take a vacation from the studio grind and are chased (on location) all over the French Capital by beautiful girls and gendarme.

episodes.name: Monkees Mind Their Manor
episodes.overview: Davy inherits an English manor but must first win a tournament against Sir Twiggley Toppen Middle Bottom (Bernard Fox) with lances, swords and vocal cords.

episodes.name: Some Like it Lukewarm (a.k.a. The Band Contest)
episodes.overview: To enter and win a band contest hosted by radio DJ Jerry Blavat, David poses as a girl and falls in love with Daphne (Deana Martin), posing as a boy for her group who is also in the contest.

episodes.name: Monkees Blow Their Minds
episodes.overview: The Monkees swing to the rescue when mentalist Oracullo (Monte Landis) gains control of Peter's mind to use him in a nightclub act. Director James Frawley appears as Oracullo's assistant Rudy.

episodes.name: Mijacogeo (a.k.a. The Frodis Caper)
episodes.overview: The Monkees match wits with the insane Wizard Glick (Rip Taylor), who is out to control the minds of television viewers worldwide.
